-- Agribank to Boost Agricultural, Small-Company Loans, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-01-30T15:58:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/agribank-to-boost-agricultural-small-company-loans-xinhua-says.html
Agricultural Bank of China Ltd. , the
nation’s fourth-largest lender, will offer more credit to
support agriculture and small and micro enterprises, Xinhua News
Agency said, citing Chairman Jiang Chaoliang.  Lending will be focused especially on irrigation and water
conservation, and on projects that boost farmers’ incomes, the
official news service said. Outstanding loans to small and micro
enterprises stood at 575.2 billion yuan ($91 billion) on Dec.
31, up 25 percent on year, according to Xinhua.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
